# Keel Project Rules

## Tech Stack
- Frontend: Vite + React 19 + TypeScript + TailwindCSS v4
- Backend: Express 5 + TypeScript (ESM)
- Database: PostgreSQL + Drizzle ORM
- Auth: BetterAuth

## Critical Rules
- ALL TypeScript imports MUST use .js extension (ESM): import { x } from "./foo.js"
- Shared types: import from "@keel/shared"
- Backend routes use requireAuth middleware for protected endpoints
- Frontend uses useAuth() hook for auth state
- TailwindCSS theme colors: keel-navy, keel-blue, keel-gray-{50,100,400,800,900}

## Adding Features
- New route: packages/backend/src/routes/<name>.ts, mount in index.ts before // [SAIL_ROUTES]
- New page: packages/frontend/src/pages/<Name>.tsx, add to router.tsx
- New table: packages/backend/src/db/schema/<name>.ts, export from index.ts, run db:generate + db:migrate
- New email: packages/email/src/<name>.tsx, export from index.ts

## Verification
After any change, run: npm run check
